pull_request.title: Update Chromium build instructions
pull_request.body:
* Add instructions to build Chromium on Windows
  - Add QUIC support to the OQS-Chromium (currently quantum safe KEX cannot be used with QUIC on OQS-Chromium)
  - Add quantum safe signature support to QOS-Chromium (solve issue #111 )
* A prebuilt 64-bit Windows Chromium installer can be found [here](https://filebin.net/vjpj3eo13yb3tes2). Note: oqstest_CA is hard coded into the source code of this Chromium

pull_request.body:
<!-- Please give a brief explanation of the purpose of this pull request. -->
1. Add common macOS filetype to .gitignore to avoid accidental checkins
2. Add visual studio code / jetbrains IDE config file location to .gitignore as above
3. Correction to readme - path to generated documentation was incorrect

Both are very minor, but things I noticed when using liboqs for the first time, and walking through the documentation.
Hope this really small contribution helps & is appropriate.

I can also squash or re-edit to follow appropriate guidelines if needed
